This paper is about task-oriented dialogue systems, which are a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The proposed method uses attention mechanism and seq2seq learning, which are common techniques in NLP and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP and computational linguistics. The second most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers topics related to AI and machine learning. The third most likely category is cs.LG (Learning), which covers topics related to machine learning and deep learning. The fourth most likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), which covers topics related to software development and engineering. The fifth most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which covers topics related to neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
